==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unclothe
<hw>Un*clothe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>clothe</ets>.]</ety> <def>To strip of clothes or
covering; to make naked.</def> <rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[We] do groan being burdened; not for that we would be
<qex>unclothed</qex>, but clothed upon.</q> <rj><qau>2 Cor. v.
4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unclothed</ent>⟦br⟧
